						               													<description>Draw a category and compose a themed word ... but be careful: you only win if you form the longest word and use the least used letters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players draw 5 letter tiles per color from the dealer (5 blue, 5 green and 5 red, in total 15).  The current player draws a category map.  All the players at this point must form, with the available letters, a word that belongs to the extracted category.  &amp;#10;When one of the contestants thinks he has formed a correct word, he counts up to 15 and at that point the game stops and points are calculated.  It then continues with a new heat.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At each new round each competitor can decide to draw a new letter, but he must discard one of the same color (putting it back in the middle).  The game always continues in the same way: the winner is whoever reaches 50 points (or more, or less, at the choice of the players).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
